     NAME
         CPU_AllocResource - This function attempts to gain ownership 
                             of the specified feature/resource of the 
                             CPU for the caller.

     SYNOPSIS
         char *__asm CPU_AllocResource(register __d0 ULONG rescode,
                                       register __a0 char *name)

      FUNCTION
         This function attempts to gain ownership of the specified
         feature/resource of the CPU for the caller.  If somebody else
         has it already, their name is returned.  If the caller gets the
         resource, NULL is returned and the name provided is associated
         with the resource.

      INPUTS
         rescode - code indicating desired resource
         name    - name to be associated with resource

      RESULTS
         user - NULL if the resource was available, else the name
                of the current owner.

      SEE ALSO
         CPU_FreeResource 

/*page*/

     NAME
         CPU_FreeResource - Relinquishes ownership of a feature 
                            (resource) of the CPU.

     SYNOPSIS
         void __asm CPU_FreeResource(register __d0 ULONG rescode)

      FUNCTION
         Relinquishes ownership of a feature (resource) of the CPU.
         This resource must have been previously allocated via
         CPU_AllocResource.

      INPUTS
         rescode - code indicating resource to free.

      SEE ALSO
         CPU_AllocResource 

