     NAME
         CPU_GetChar - Blocking fetch of a character from the indicated 
                       serial port. This is a low-level, non-interrupt, 
                       non-arbitrated procedure.

     SYNOPSIS
         UBYTE __asm CPU_GetChar(register __d0 BYTE port)

      FUNCTION
         Blocking fetch of a character from the indicated serial port.
         This is a low-level, non-interrupt, non-arbitrated procedure.
         The port must have previously been configured appropriately.

      INPUTS
         port - 0 or 1

      RESULTS
         b - the character fetched 

/*page*/

     NAME
         CPU_GetSerialSettings - Read settings for serial port - kinda.

     SYNOPSIS
         void __asm CPU_GetSerialSettings(register __d0 UBYTE port,
                                          register __a0 struct 
                                          SerialSettings *settings)

      FUNCTION
         Read settings for serial port - kinda.  This function fetches
         the settings last applied to the port by SetPortSettings.
         That means that the settings returned are not valid if they
         have been changed without the use of SetPortSettings.

      INPUTS
         port     - 0 or 1
         settings - ptr to a SerialSettings struct where the "current"
                    settings will be returned. 

/*page*/

     NAME
         CPU_PutChar - Write a character to the indicated serial port.

     SYNOPSIS
         void __asm CPU_PutChar(register __d0 BYTE port, 
                                register __d1 UBYTE b)

      FUNCTION
         Write a character to the indicated serial port.  This is
         a low-level, non-interrupt, non-arbitrated procedure.  This
         procedure busy waits for transmission to complete.  The
         port must have previously been configured appropriately.

      INPUTS
         port - 0 or 1
         b    - character to output 

/*page*/

     NAME
         CPU_ReadChar - Reads a character from the indicated serial 
                        port.

     SYNOPSIS
         BOOL __asm CPU_ReadChar(register __d0 BYTE port, 
                                 register __a0 UBYTE *b)

      FUNCTION
         Reads a character from the indicated serial port.  This is
         a low-level, non-interrupt, non-arbitrated, non-blocking
         procedure. The port must have previously been configured
         appropriately.

      INPUTS
         port - 0 or 1
         b    - ptr to storage for character read

      RESULTS
         read - TRUE means a character was read. 

/*page*/

     NAME
         CPU_SetSerialSettings - Modify settings for serial port.

     SYNOPSIS
         void __asm CPU_SetSerialSettings(register __d0 UBYTE port,
                                          register __a0 struct 
                                          SerialSettings *settings)

      FUNCTION
         Modify settings for serial port.  This function provides a
         comfortable method for setting up most aspects of a serial port.
         This function is not for use where speed is of concern.  For
         instance it is not intended to replace knowledge of hardware
         specifics on the part of the serial device.  Do not use
         this procedure in interrupt code.

      INPUTS
         port     - 0 or 1
         settings - ptr to a SerialSettings struct specifying baud
                    rate etc.

      SEE ALSO
         GetSerialSettings, resources/serial.h 

